IBADAN – The burial committee of the late former Governor of Oyo state Otunba Christopher Adebayo Alao-Akala has announced that the burial rites of the late politician will commence on February 14. The media sub-committee of the Senator Brimmo Yusuff-led committee announced that the late elder statesman and political titan’s burial arrangements will commence on Monday 14th February and end on 20th February 2022. The Bobagunwa of Ogbomosoland died on the 12th of January 2022 in Ogbomoso at the age of 71. Police Commence Enforcement Of Total Ban On Unauthorised Sirens,… Yobe Commends AFRYDEV For Training GBV Survivors The burial program according to a statement signed by the chairman, media sub-committee, Hon Segun Dokun Odebunmi, revealed that the programme will begin on Monday, 14th February 2022 with Lecture & Day of Tributes by the Political Class at Hall of Grace, Jogor Centre, Liberty Road, Ibadan, Oyo State at 11:00 am. On Tuesday, 15th February 2022 a Lecture & Day of Tributes will also hold at 1500 Lecture Theater, College of Health Science, LAUTECH, Ogbomoso, Oyo State at 10:00 am. This will be followed by a Praise Night at His residence, Opadoyin Akala Lodge, Randa Ogbomoso, Oyo State by 4:00 pm. Wednesday, 16th February 2022, there will be a Lying in State & Executive Session at House of Chiefs, Oyo State Government Secretariat, Agodi, Ibadan, Oyo State, by 12:00 pm. The burial Committee added that the Hearse afterwards will depart in a motorcade to Ogbomoso, Oyo state. POLL A cultural display and Parade will come up on Thursday, 17 February 2022, at his residence, Opadoyin Akala Lodge, Randa Ogbomoso, Oyo State, by 10:00 am. This will be followed by a Lying in state, Christian Wake Keep and Service of songs at Ogbomoso High School Open Field, Ogbomoso, Oyo State by 4:00 pm. The final Burial Service will hold on Friday, 18th February 2022 at Beulah Baptist Conference Ground, Behind Baptist High School, Ogbomoso, Oyo State, by 11:00 am. His remains will be interred immediately at his residence, Opadoyin Akala Lodge, Randa, Ogbomoso, Oyo State. Reception & Entertainment of Guests will hold at Ogbomoso Recreation Club, Ilorin Road, Ogbomoso, Oyo State. 4th Edition Of Africa Human Resources Innovation Awards (AHRIA)… Stakeholders Rue N1trn Annual Loss To Absence Of Single Window A thanksgiving service will hold at Oke-Elerin Baptist Church, Ogbomoso, Oyo State on Sunday, 20th February 2022 by 10:00 am. The chairman central planning committee Senator Brimmo Yusuff assured that adequate security measures have been put in place to ensure the safety of people and valuables during the event.